                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260112-151-off855 t18260112-151-crimeloc857"></join>, and is a <rs id="t18260112-151-viclabel858" type="occupation">butcher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260112-151-victim820 t18260112-151-viclabel858"></join>. On the 12th of December I was putting a mat down at my parlour door, and saw the prisoner come to the window and take a piece of mutton from the shop-board, and put it under her shawl. I arose up, and she walked into the shop, and asked if I had any beef-steaks. I said, "Where is the bit of mutton you took from the board;" I lifted up her shawl and saw it - she said it was not mine, she had bought it in Clare-market - I sent for the officer; she then said, "I beg your pardon, and I will pay you what you please."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260112-151-person822">
